x402.matija.eu
==============

Pay-per-request API on Cloudflare Workers using the x402 protocol.
Protected endpoints cost 1 USDC on Polygon. No API keys, no accounts
— just a wallet signature.

Live at https://x402.matija.eu


How it works
------------

  1. Client requests a protected endpoint.
  2. Server responds 402 with a PAYMENT-REQUIRED header.
  3. Client signs a gasless USDC transfer (EIP-3009) with their wallet.
  4. Client resends the request with a PAYMENT-SIGNATURE header.
  5. A facilitator verifies the signature and settles on-chain.
  6. Server returns the protected resource.

Browsers get an interactive paywall page. Programmatic clients use
the x402 SDK or handle the headers directly.


Endpoints
---------

  GET /               Man-page overview (this info, but prettier).
  GET /payment-info   Machine-readable JSON: network, token, price.
  GET /api/data       Protected. Returns example JSON. 1 USDC.
  GET /api/status     Protected. Returns server status. 1 USDC.


Stack
-----

  Runtime         Cloudflare Workers
  Framework       Hono
  Protocol        x402 v2
  Network         Polygon mainnet (eip155:137)
  Token           USDC (0x3c499c542cEF5E3811e1192ce70d8cC03d5c3359)
  Facilitator     https://facilitator.payai.network
  Paywall         Custom man-page styled HTML with wallet integration


Files
-----

  src/index.js      Hono app, routes, x402 middleware.
  src/paywall.js    Custom PaywallProvider — man-page styled 402 page
                    with EIP-3009 signing via window.ethereum.
  wrangler.toml     Cloudflare Workers config.
  package.json      Dependencies.


Development
-----------

  npm install
  npm run dev         # local dev server via wrangler

No secrets needed. The x402 facilitator handles on-chain settlement.


Deployment
----------

  npm run deploy      # deploys to Cloudflare Workers


Dependencies
------------

  @x402/core          x402 protocol core
  @x402/evm           EVM payment scheme (EIP-3009, Permit2)
  @x402/hono          Hono middleware adapter
  hono                Web framework


Links
-----

  x402 protocol       https://docs.x402.org
  Source              https://github.com/matija/x402.matija.eu
